page.title: 11Birds and Water Life
page.content: In our area we have woods,open fields and hedgerows.These make good places for birds to live.In the woods you can find jays,rooks,pigeons,woodpeckers and owls.In the fields you can see larks aand pheasants.In the hedgerows live blackbirds,thrushes and starlings.Around the houses you can see swallows,house martins,swifts and common garden birds. The River Great Stour flows swiftly through our area.There are lots of ditches and drains running into the river,they are mainly slow moving or stagnant.In the river there are fresh water fish such as minnows,crayfish and pike.In the ditches live diving beetles,frogs,scavenger boatmen, dragonflies and snails.We found a thin film of diesel on the surface of the ditches.
